verbose_text: The model predicts the degree to which VEGF concentrations beyond an activation threshold influence total vessel length changes, ranks the key individual factors in migration and proliferation by differentiating tip and stalk cell events, explores three potential mechanisms altering cellular persistence, offers one perspective on how branching and vessel length changes could be correlated and predicts global angiogenic changes to knockout conditions both knockouts at the level of Dll4 receptor binding and cell specific processes.
